==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indigence
<hw>In"di*gence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indigentia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>indigence</ets>. See
<er>Indigent</er>.]</ety> <def>The condition of being indigent; lack of
estate, or means of comfortable subsistence; penury; poverty; <as>as,
helpless <ex>indigence</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Poverty; penury; destitution; want; need;
privation; lack. See <er>Poverty</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indigency</ent>⟦br⟧
